 96→/**
 97→ * Starts a long running (application) Thread that will run through commands
 98→ * that require remote mailbox access. This class is used to serialize and
 99→ * prioritize these commands. Each method that will submit a command requires a
100→ * MessagingListener instance to be provided. It is expected that that listener
101→ * has also been added as a registered listener using addListener(). When a
102→ * command is to be executed, if the listener that was provided with the command
103→ * is no longer registered the command is skipped. The design idea for the above
104→ * is that when an Activity starts it registers as a listener. When it is paused
105→ * it removes itself. Thus, any commands that that activity submitted are
106→ * removed from the queue once the activity is no longer active.
107→ */
